After the Tuesday morning siege laid to his residence by security operatives, Senate President Bukola Saraki, eventually made his way to the Senate chamber and he is currently presiding over the day’s plenary session. The Deputy Senate President, Senator Ike Ekweremadu, is however absent as security operatives continue to lay siege to his residence in Apo. Ekweremadu’s Media Adviser, Mr. Uche Anichukwu, told THISDAY that his boss was at home as his residence was still under siege by security operatives. Details later…